# ─── Match Center — environment ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to `.env` (git-ignored) and adjust for your machine. Only variables
# prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ are inlined into the client bundle by Expo at build
# time (see https://docs.expo.dev/guides/environment-variables/).

# Base URL of the @matchcenter/api backend (services/api) the app talks to for
# all REST reads (/v1/…) and the live WebSocket (ws(s)://…/v1/live/ws). No
# trailing slash — it's stripped anyway. The WS base is derived automatically
# (http→ws, https→wss) in lib/api/config.ts.
#
#   • Read at build time by lib/api/config.ts.
#   • If unset, the app falls back to the dev default below — the LAN address a
#     simulator/device on the same network can reach during local development.
#     Change 10.0.0.195 to YOUR machine's LAN IP (a device can't reach
#     localhost/127.0.0.1 on your dev box).
#   • Point at your deployed backend for staging/production builds, e.g.
#     EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.matchcenter.example.com
#
# NOTE: if the backend is unreachable, every repointed hook transparently falls
# back to hitting ESPN directly, so the app still renders (see lib/api/adapters).
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.0.195:8080
